{
  "texts": [
    "In agriculture, AI is being applied to address challenges such as popula-tion growth, climate change, and food security (Patel and Patil 2022; Liu 2020; Sahoo and Sharma 2023).",
    "Through the integration of AI technologies like computer vision, machine learning, and predictive analytics, agricultural practices are becoming more efficient and productive.",
    "AI applications in agriculture include automated weeding, pesticide spraying using drones, livestock monitoring, disease detection in crops and animals, and soil analysis (Patel and Patil 2022).",
    "These technologies not only enhance productivity but also contribute to sustainability by reducing resource usage, improving soil health, and mitigating the impact of climate change on farming practices (Sahoo and Sharma 2023).",
    "Blockchain technology Combining blockchain technology with the Internet of Things enables end-to-end visibility, real-time monitoring, and immutable record-keeping of food products, addressing challenges such as food fraud, traceability, and sustainability."
  ]
}